  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Once cooked, remove from the heat and transfer to a plate and spread it out flat to help the rice cool down</span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> into cubes </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cubed pork</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>smoked <span class=\"text-highlight\">paprika</span></strong>, <strong>Chinese five-spice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the pork is coated in the spices</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching <span class=\"text-highlight\">lid),</span> over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>cubed pork</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until browned<span class=\"text-highlight\"> - this is your <strong>five-spiced pork</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC804Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has browned, add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>soy sauce </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p>\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce is sticky and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!<br /><br /><br /></p>",
